I was at Seneca reviewing a group project and simultaneusly browsing through some random journals. NEVER AGAIN. I felt sick in the stomach when I saw these. I was like a deer caught in the lights of the on-coming truck, stuck, unable to move away, trying to make sense of what I saw.

It was a journal that had pictures of dead decomposing grown dogs and puppies. The pictures began with writings on walls  telling to find and keep the dogs. Then the next pictures where of already dead dogs. *shakes head* I wish I didn't stay long enough to make sense of the decomposed jaws and stomachs. I didn't see everything .. I couldn't take it .. why would someone post this? There's probably a story behind it, hopefully. I didn't stick around to find out.

Coward? Maybe. But I would rather not let my imagination be joined with these images especially with my now sick cat..

sworn off random journals

I had an adventure on Friday evening. 

Me, Artie, and Nir(his friend from Israel that came for a visit) went to Metro, which was half empty by the way. We had fun, danced some, the music pretty much sucked no matter which room or floor we went to, nevertheless it was entertaining to a point. 
*sighs*
We left around 3:30 am to catch the Bathurst bus. 30 minutes went by before the bus could be seen with it's headlights shining about 3-4 blocks away. This is when things got bad. 
55 year-old white dude, and 30~ish black guy; both drug dealers, one owns the other one 20 bucks. 20 FUCKING DOLLARS!!!! A fight begins, first there's the regular macho swearing/pushing bravado. The bus nears and people walk around the fighting couple to get closer to the road. Obviously, not much time passes before a few more guys get involved with overly crude comments. We get on the bus everything seems fine. The fight has yet to escalate into anything more concrete. Suddenly people are running towards the bus's rear doors, pounding on them. The white dude is bloodied (did you have any doubts?!). The commentary guys decide that they had enough of a show and head for the now open rear doors (thinking they'd catch a free ride), unfortunately the black dealer follows, white dude close behind him. 
Guess where we are sitting.. Yep, in the back. 
As the two dealers enter pushing and shoving, elbows to the sides, the crowd flows in the opposite direction getting off the bus. We can't follow, the fighting men are blocking the exit. The commentary guys get involved more physically, things are not looking up.
A number of people that stayed in the front continuously tug on the stop bell making the bus's lights blink, while the few of us in the back resort on pounding on the back window glass to catch the attention of a passing police car. 
The policeman goes up, we go down.  The bus goes out of service. 
Ten minutes later, a ttc service car arrives and talks over with the driver and the policeman allowing us finally to go back on the bus.
But the story doesn't stop there.
It is 4:30 in the morning. The bus drives away. Five minutes pass before the driver announces that the bus is overloaded and some people will have to get off. Two more minutes and the bus is proclaimed to be broken. For a while people simply refuse to get off, but finally see that they have no choice. 
A short wait after another bus arrives. At 5:45 we are finally at home, and  asleep. 

Now that was a nasty, very nasty experience. So I thought I'd share :D

*runs to class*

Your Pisces Drinking Style
If you're a Pisces, you've probably already heard that you share a sign -- and an addictive personality -- with Liz Taylor, Liza Minelli and Kurt Cobain. Not only do Pisces like to lose themselves in the dreamy, out-there feeling that only hooch can give, but you build up a mighty tolerance fast. You're an expensive date! On the other hand, you're a fabulously enchanting partner, whether in conversation or in crime. With the right person, you can start out sharing a pitcher of margaritas and wind up in bed together for days. The phrase "addictive personality" can be read two ways, you know.
Your Signature Cocktails
Pisces rules fresh mint, and you do love a mojito or three -- though a julep will do just as well. You also like punches, like sangria or the oh-so-aptly named fish house punch. (Pretty much anything will satisfy a Pisces in a pinch, though -- "drinking like a fish" is an idiom pulled out of the zodiac, not the deep blue sea.) You're a total chocoholic, and you love creme de cacao (and spiked cocoa).

Yet another month has passed.

I have finally renewed my contract with the background acting agency... which of course is again trying to rip me off.. but I guess some dreams take longer time to die and our mistakes have to be larger than usually to actually teach our minds not to do them again....

But there is a ray of light in the darkness for me, as a modeling agency had sought me out, I'll be meeting with them most probably a week after this one, and hopefully it will result in a good and prosperous deal between us.

My boyfriend, bless his soul no matter how much he annoys me, had finally brought some peace to my wandering mind. Perhaps we shall settle down sooner than we thought or mayhaps we will get accustomed to each other and will learn to compromise, although that was not the case between us for the past three years. Who knows.. we have grown after all.

My studies are interesting and boring, they bring to me delight and constant headaches. But it will be worth it in the end... I know it.. even if I feel that there is more out there for me that I should be doing, I believe it will come to me with time. For now, I should be happy with what I have and seek information and the means to acquire what it is I will want to do in the later future.

Magic.... Energy... I do not know if I will pursue it nor if I will have the strength to follow the rightful path and decipher whether or not I will be hurting anyone..... tis hard... and requires patience that I will need to seek very deep within myself.

Only time will tell.

~Rya

I've had a weekend full of "wonderful" revelations. I would tell you about it, but it is inappropriate. So, I will only describe the feeling that the situation has created; something along the lines of loss, and despair, fear for what my arise from future situations like this, as I know that if I get involved in it, and not simply bare witness to it, I will end up doing something drastic.

Why do people fight? 

Well, yes there is the lack of understanding, simply bad mood, or in some cases pms (yea yea), in other cases people get provoked. But in the end it all comes down to patience or the lack thereof. And it is not just patience in general, you could push around a monk and he will tell you to pray, but if you curse his blessed wine you have crossed the line :).

Every one of us has a border for all possible issues that could be matters of opinion. In the end everything comes down to this. 

It is a husband that cheats on his wife as his patience for her lack of attention has disappeared. It is a wife that takes back her husband that has committed adultery, as her patience for him has gone thin but she has some still left in her. 
It is the baby that cries for toys and the mother that buys the toys as she has no patience to wait out the wailing. 
Oh I know these are controversial thoughts, however they work both ways.
Because in the end the patience in almost every case is mixed with emotions: love, hate, like, dislike, pity...

You find yourself raised in certain conditions and for a slight moment you think that the rest of the world is like that. Of course then your mother takes you out on your first trip to the playground and Johnny steals your doll, which evidently shakes your world to its core. 

What happens when as an adult you realize that there is absolutely no one, not even remotely close, that has the exact same morals, and values as you. And at that same moment you are thrown in to an environment, which present you with so many untouchable challenges that your first reaction is to run away, hide, and pretend that none of this other stuff exists. Yet you find yourself sticking around, taking in more and more of the so called other realm of living. 

None of us can ever truly change, but we can learn to visually bend, and make the other people (the rest of the world), think that we did. Yet our mind will keep treading along the same path.

*sighs* Enough, I am just babling, babling about things that in more ways then one will forever remain unpredictable. As we are all unique, and I can only hope that I will find away to co exist with people so very different from me. 

~Rya

I'm in that mood again. You know, the one that makes you seek a very, very dark corner and curl into a tiny ball. Or maybe run outside and scream until your lose your voice. It is the mood that comes from both boredom and the knowledge that you have an infinite amount of things to do but do not wish to do any of them. The company of your friends will suffocate you and the lack of company at all will make you seek out a good computer game, or a tv show. Which of course you will not watch/play until the end because you will lose interest in the first five minutes. You begin to read a book and the words blure before your eyes, you decide to study but your mind drifts to a different place. You dream up different ways to torture all the people that claim that they are cheerful today and watch as misery in which you are engulfed seek out company in all possible places and people. Now, how to name this mood I do not know, as it is not depression, nor loneliness, or boredom. So here I share it with you, with the rationale of escaping the void inside my mind. ~Rya

Begins to count...... OMG 12 hours LOL Yesterday, I came back home from college did the regular things, had a dinner. And with full intention of getting to the projects, and the tests, I lied down on the bed, closed my eyes... and slept for 12 freaking hours.... I got on the bed at six in the evening and I woke up at six in the morning running to get ready for college. But damn it felt so very very very good. All warm and cuddly. Talking about warm and cuddly, every time I sleep over at my boyfriends or visa versa.. when it is time to sleep I find us going through the same pattern: we hug, kiss, talk, argue, and warm up to each other; HOWEVER when it comes to the actual sleeping we both hog the bed covers, twist and turn, pound the pillows etc' etc' etc' And I've been with my boyfriend for three years!! "Frailty thy name is woman" or so you say. In present day you are, as you define me. What happened to your manly, so-called might? Me think it's far from earth by now.
